      </div>
    </div>
        <div class="blog-content__metadata blog-content__metadata-author">
      <span class="blog-content__date">  <time datetime="2020-12-02T15:24:19Z">December 02, 2020</time>

</span>
        <span class="blog-content__author">
                Proofpoint Threat Research Team
  
        </span>
    </div>
    <div class="node-full__body blog-content__body">  <p paraeid="{6a703b0e-c80a-4344-bef7-10409b7555d3}{128}" paraid="952367335">In&nbsp;November&nbsp;2019 Proofpoint researchers uncovered email campaigns distributing&nbsp;NetWire, a widely used RAT.&nbsp;The&nbsp;campaigns used&nbsp;Bulgarian&nbsp;language lures, narrow geo targeting, geofencing, and&nbsp;had&nbsp;low&nbsp;message volume.&nbsp;Since then, Proofpoint has identified additional campaigns with&nbsp;matching&nbsp;attributes,&nbsp;including:&nbsp;&nbsp;Bulgarian&nbsp;language&nbsp;email lures,&nbsp;a&nbsp;NetWire&nbsp;payload, the Command and Control (C2) domain,&nbsp;malware config password, and the Microsoft Word document author "vps".&nbsp;NetWire&nbsp;has been a widely employed tool since inception in 2002,&nbsp;offering&nbsp;malware for multiple operating systems, including Windows, MacOS, and Linux. The RAT&nbsp;is&nbsp;sold in&nbsp;underground forums&nbsp;for&nbsp;between&nbsp;$40&nbsp;and&nbsp;$140&nbsp;dollars.&nbsp;</p>

<h3 paraeid="{6a703b0e-c80a-4344-bef7-10409b7555d3}{244}" paraid="1523427680">Targeting and Email Lures&nbsp;</h3>

<p paraeid="{6a703b0e-c80a-4344-bef7-10409b7555d3}{250}" paraid="167315431">In October and early November&nbsp;2020,&nbsp;Proofpoint researchers observed&nbsp;multiple&nbsp;low volume&nbsp;campaigns&nbsp;intended&nbsp;for&nbsp;less than 10 companies&nbsp;in the&nbsp;Aerospace, Industrial,&nbsp;Manufacturing, Construction, Energy, Financial Transaction Services, and Business Services verticals.&nbsp;While the spread&nbsp;across sectors&nbsp;in these campaigns&nbsp;is&nbsp;diverse, all companies have&nbsp;business operations&nbsp;in Bulgaria.&nbsp;Some&nbsp;have&nbsp;a&nbsp;supplier&nbsp;relationship to larger energy&nbsp;projects&nbsp;and aerospace&nbsp;manufacturing initiatives.&nbsp;The&nbsp;latest&nbsp;activity&nbsp;diverges&nbsp;in scope and scale&nbsp;from&nbsp;a&nbsp;previously observed&nbsp;NetWire&nbsp;campaign&nbsp;in June which delivered&nbsp;approximately&nbsp;500 messages&nbsp;to&nbsp;about&nbsp;150 customers&nbsp;across&nbsp;40&nbsp;verticals. That campaign&nbsp;was written in&nbsp;Bulgarian&nbsp;and leveraged&nbsp;themes from the largest national bank,&nbsp;Bulbank.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>

<p paraeid="{fabb039b-bb43-4408-8565-d6c81fc1cf35}{163}" paraid="1055619666">The&nbsp;current&nbsp;campaigns&nbsp;also&nbsp;are&nbsp;localized, in Bulgarian, and claim to include financial information or&nbsp;a&nbsp;notification of an&nbsp;open&nbsp;enforcement case initiated against the recipient.&nbsp;Two&nbsp;email&nbsp;campaigns&nbsp;later in October&nbsp;impersonated the Sofia Court House based out of Bulgaria.&nbsp;In the latest&nbsp;November campaign, one of the aerospace technology organizations was targeted again from October in a single phish and leveraging both spoofed infrastructure and&nbsp;document file name of the Bulgarian national Commission for Combating Corruption and Confiscation of Illegally Acquired Property (KPKONPI).&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>

<p paraeid="{fabb039b-bb43-4408-8565-d6c81fc1cf35}{215}" paraid="821907630">Below&nbsp;is an example of&nbsp;message characteristics observed in November&nbsp;2019:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>

<ul>
	<li paraeid="{fabb039b-bb43-4408-8565-d6c81fc1cf35}{229}" paraid="1115203280">From: &lt;&nbsp;bulgaria@caciaf[.]bg&nbsp;&gt;&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>
	<li paraeid="{fabb039b-bb43-4408-8565-d6c81fc1cf35}{250}" paraid="986642317">Subject:&nbsp;Деклариране&nbsp;на&nbsp;финансови&nbsp;активи&nbsp;("Declaration of financial assets")&nbsp;</li>
	<li paraeid="{eea8a17c-1116-450a-b502-86352a2b1093}{20}" paraid="1125285613">Attachments: kpkonpi_dv86.doc&nbsp;</li>
</ul>

<p paraeid="{eea8a17c-1116-450a-b502-86352a2b1093}{27}" paraid="1427235139">&nbsp;&nbsp;<img src="data:image/png;base64," unselectable="on"></p>

<p paraeid="{eea8a17c-1116-450a-b502-86352a2b1093}{27}" paraid="1427235139"><em>Figure 1:&nbsp;Microsoft Word attachment with enable&nbsp;macros&nbsp;message&nbsp;</em></p>

<p paraeid="{eea8a17c-1116-450a-b502-86352a2b1093}{54}" paraid="288344096">&nbsp;Below&nbsp;is an example of&nbsp;message characteristics observed in January&nbsp;2020:&nbsp;</p>

<ul>
	<li paraeid="{eea8a17c-1116-450a-b502-86352a2b1093}{72}" paraid="210818761">From:&nbsp;Пътна&nbsp;полиция&nbsp;МВР &lt;opp@mvr[.]bg&gt;&nbsp;(“Road Police MBP&nbsp;pp@mvr[.]bg”)&nbsp;</li>
	<li paraeid="{eea8a17c-1116-450a-b502-86352a2b1093}{105}" paraid="787393131">Subject:&nbsp;Призовка&nbsp;за&nbsp;явяване&nbsp;в КАТ&nbsp;("Summons to appear at the Traffic Police")&nbsp;</li>
	<li paraeid="{eea8a17c-1116-450a-b502-86352a2b1093}{128}" paraid="816360876">Attachments:&nbsp;prizovka_081419.doc&nbsp;</li>
</ul>

<p paraeid="{eea8a17c-1116-450a-b502-86352a2b1093}{141}" paraid="394758766">Below is an example of the email lure&nbsp;and message characteristics&nbsp;spotted in early October&nbsp;2020:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>

<ul>
	<li paraeid="{eea8a17c-1116-450a-b502-86352a2b1093}{155}" paraid="1430286423">From: ЧСИ&nbsp;Галин&nbsp;Костов&nbsp;&lt;kostov@gkostov[.]com&gt;&nbsp;("Private Enforcement Agent Galin Kostov")&nbsp;</li>
	<li paraeid="{eea8a17c-1116-450a-b502-86352a2b1093}{198}" paraid="1585847745">Subject:&nbsp;Уведомление&nbsp;за&nbsp;образувано&nbsp;дело&nbsp;("Notification of initiated case")&nbsp;</li>
	<li paraeid="{eea8a17c-1116-450a-b502-86352a2b1093}{223}" paraid="29695383">Attachments:&nbsp;Уведомление&nbsp;за&nbsp;&nbsp;образувано&nbsp;дело&nbsp;DELO20205593.doc&nbsp;("Notification of initiated case DELO20205593.doc")&nbsp;</li>
</ul>

<p paraeid="{eea8a17c-1116-450a-b502-86352a2b1093}{254}" paraid="445725439">&nbsp;<img src="data:image/png;base64," unselectable="on"></p>

<p paraeid="{eea8a17c-1116-450a-b502-86352a2b1093}{254}" paraid="445725439"><em>Figure 2: Bulgarian language email lure&nbsp;</em></p>

<p paraeid="{075e8591-b2ef-4369-afd5-d0e340b03ae4}{14}" paraid="209118369">Message&nbsp;body, translated from Bulgarian:&nbsp;</p>

<p paraeid="{075e8591-b2ef-4369-afd5-d0e340b03ae4}{28}" paraid="922206097"><em>Hello,&nbsp;</em></p>

<p paraeid="{075e8591-b2ef-4369-afd5-d0e340b03ae4}{34}" paraid="1566076261"><em>&nbsp;&nbsp;</em></p>

<p paraeid="{075e8591-b2ef-4369-afd5-d0e340b03ae4}{40}" paraid="1235607730"><em>With the present and on the basis. Art. 458 of the Civil Procedure Code in connection with Art. 191, para 3 of TPSC, I would like to inform you that an enforcement case has been initiated against you, pursuant to the Civil Procedure Code, in view of your outstanding liabilities to Telecom Group AD. In the attached document, you can get acquainted with the writ of execution issued by the Sofia City Court, as well as with the terms for enforcement, which will start running.&nbsp;</em></p>

<p paraeid="{075e8591-b2ef-4369-afd5-d0e340b03ae4}{70}" paraid="1952442500"><em>Private bailiff reg. №854&nbsp;</em></p>

<p paraeid="{075e8591-b2ef-4369-afd5-d0e340b03ae4}{76}" paraid="1792879905"><em>Area of operation&nbsp;</em></p>

<p paraeid="{075e8591-b2ef-4369-afd5-d0e340b03ae4}{82}" paraid="1147796164"><em>Sofia City Court&nbsp;</em></p>

<p paraeid="{075e8591-b2ef-4369-afd5-d0e340b03ae4}{88}" paraid="1576827865"><em>Tel.&nbsp;[redacted]&nbsp;</em></p>

<p paraeid="{075e8591-b2ef-4369-afd5-d0e340b03ae4}{104}" paraid="267502449">&nbsp;<img src="data:image/png;base64," unselectable="on">&nbsp;<br>

<p paraeid="{075e8591-b2ef-4369-afd5-d0e340b03ae4}{129}" paraid="1608998476">Below is an example of the email lure&nbsp;and message characteristics&nbsp;spotted&nbsp;a few days later in October&nbsp;2020.&nbsp;</p>

<ul role="list">
	<li aria-setsize="-1" data-aria-level="1" data-aria-posinset="1" data-font="Symbol" data-leveltext="" data-listid="8" role="listitem">
	<p paraeid="{075e8591-b2ef-4369-afd5-d0e340b03ae4}{143}" paraid="567662667">From: ЧСИ&nbsp;Галин&nbsp;Костов&nbsp;&lt;&nbsp;kostov@gkostov[.]com&nbsp;&gt;&nbsp;("Private Enforcement Agent Galin Kostov")&nbsp;</p>

	<li aria-setsize="-1" data-aria-level="1" data-aria-posinset="2" data-font="Symbol" data-leveltext="" data-listid="3" role="listitem">

	</li>
	<li aria-setsize="-1" data-aria-level="1" data-aria-posinset="3" data-font="Symbol" data-leveltext="" data-listid="3" role="listitem">

	</li>
</ul>

<p paraeid="{075e8591-b2ef-4369-afd5-d0e340b03ae4}{204}" paraid="29955803">&nbsp;<img src="data:image/png;base64," unselectable="on">&nbsp;</p>

<p paraeid="{075e8591-b2ef-4369-afd5-d0e340b03ae4}{211}" paraid="1596162253"><em>Figure 4: Bulgarian language email lure&nbsp;</em></p>

<p paraeid="{075e8591-b2ef-4369-afd5-d0e340b03ae4}{217}" paraid="1842591252">Message&nbsp;body, translated from Bulgarian:&nbsp;</p>

<p paraeid="{075e8591-b2ef-4369-afd5-d0e340b03ae4}{229}" paraid="40700312"><em>Hello,&nbsp;</em></p>

<p paraeid="{075e8591-b2ef-4369-afd5-d0e340b03ae4}{235}" paraid="988211575"><em>With the present and on the basis. Art. 458 of the Civil Procedure Code in connection with Art. 191, para 3 of TPSC, I would like to inform you that an enforcement case has been initiated against you, pursuant to the Civil Procedure Code, in view of your outstanding liabilities to Telecom Group AD. In the attached document, you can get acquainted with the writ of execution issued by the Sofia City Court, as well as with the terms for enforcement, which will start running.&nbsp;</em></p>

<p paraeid="{075e8591-b2ef-4369-afd5-d0e340b03ae4}{241}" paraid="1781130761"><em>With respect,&nbsp;</em></p>

<p paraeid="{075e8591-b2ef-4369-afd5-d0e340b03ae4}{247}" paraid="473154309"><em>Galin Kostov&nbsp;</em></p>

<p paraeid="{075e8591-b2ef-4369-afd5-d0e340b03ae4}{253}" paraid="1169347987"><em>Private bailiff reg. №854&nbsp;</em></p>

<p paraeid="{4dd69d79-2a25-469b-b34e-ebb94eb65cd2}{4}" paraid="537997240"><em>Area of operation&nbsp;</em></p>

<p paraeid="{4dd69d79-2a25-469b-b34e-ebb94eb65cd2}{10}" paraid="1671053528"><em>Sofia City Court&nbsp;</em></p>

<p paraeid="{4dd69d79-2a25-469b-b34e-ebb94eb65cd2}{16}" paraid="285244968">Tel.&nbsp;[redacted]&nbsp;</p>

<p paraeid="{4dd69d79-2a25-469b-b34e-ebb94eb65cd2}{24}" paraid="1654493457">&nbsp;</p>

<p paraeid="{4dd69d79-2a25-469b-b34e-ebb94eb65cd2}{24}" paraid="1654493457"><img src="data:image/png;base64," unselectable="on"></p>

<p paraeid="{4dd69d79-2a25-469b-b34e-ebb94eb65cd2}{24}" paraid="1654493457"><em>Figure 5: Microsoft Word attachment with enable&nbsp;macros&nbsp;message&nbsp;</em></p>

<p paraeid="{4dd69d79-2a25-469b-b34e-ebb94eb65cd2}{43}" paraid="1811265482">Each of the email lures observed contained Microsoft Word documents with&nbsp;macros.&nbsp;Additionally, the Microsoft Word documents&nbsp;included the same&nbsp;text box&nbsp;describing&nbsp;the&nbsp;Office document&nbsp;as protected,&nbsp;along with&nbsp;instructions on how to enable editing&nbsp;and enable&nbsp;content&nbsp;for viewing.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>

<h3 paraeid="{4dd69d79-2a25-469b-b34e-ebb94eb65cd2}{87}" paraid="1673065519">Installation and Payload&nbsp;</h3>

<p paraeid="{4dd69d79-2a25-469b-b34e-ebb94eb65cd2}{93}" paraid="1837227012">Analysis of the Microsoft Word attachments shows that the macros, if enabled, conditionally load&nbsp;NetWire.&nbsp;Geofencing, or restricting access to content based on the user’s&nbsp;location,&nbsp;was observed in these campaigns.&nbsp;Specifically, the execution and download of&nbsp;NetWire&nbsp;occurs only&nbsp;if the&nbsp;user’s IP address&nbsp;is based&nbsp;in&nbsp;Bulgaria,&nbsp;otherwise,&nbsp;a 403 error will be displayed.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>

<p paraeid="{4dd69d79-2a25-469b-b34e-ebb94eb65cd2}{153}" paraid="517158491">Interestingly, the Microsoft Word documents shared the same&nbsp;“author”&nbsp;and&nbsp;“last saved by”&nbsp;value,&nbsp;which was “vps”.&nbsp;</p>

<p paraeid="{4dd69d79-2a25-469b-b34e-ebb94eb65cd2}{181}" paraid="105368972">When the attachment is opened and macros enabled, the VBA macro within the Microsoft Word attachment will execute the built-in Microsoft tool&nbsp;<a href="https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0160/ " target="_blank">certutil</a>&nbsp;to download&nbsp;the&nbsp;NetWire&nbsp;payload.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Microsoft tool&nbsp;certutil&nbsp;can be used with the&nbsp;urlcache&nbsp;and split&nbsp;flags&nbsp;to download&nbsp;and save a file to a specified directory.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>

<p paraeid="{4dd69d79-2a25-469b-b34e-ebb94eb65cd2}{231}" paraid="471481587">Sample&nbsp;certutil&nbsp;downloading commands:&nbsp;</p>

<p paraeid="{4dd69d79-2a25-469b-b34e-ebb94eb65cd2}{251}" paraid="1860045196"><img src="data:image/png;base64," unselectable="on">&nbsp;</p>

<h3 paraeid="{4dd69d79-2a25-469b-b34e-ebb94eb65cd2}{251}" paraid="1860045196">Malware Configuration&nbsp;and Persistence&nbsp;</h3>

<p paraeid="{3a92dc90-05dc-453c-85a4-efacb23a9cd3}{9}" paraid="1414298169">NetWire&nbsp;is a multi-platform remote access tool (RAT) developed by&nbsp;<a href="https://www.cyberscoop.com/world-wired-labs-winnti-netwire-china-blackberry-cylance/" target="_blank">World Wired Labs</a>&nbsp;since&nbsp;2012.&nbsp;NetWire&nbsp;gives&nbsp;threat actors&nbsp;several features,&nbsp;including:&nbsp;</p>

<ul>
	<li paraeid="{3a92dc90-05dc-453c-85a4-efacb23a9cd3}{49}" paraid="1744451937">File Manager (download, upload, and search for files)&nbsp;</li>
	<li paraeid="{3a92dc90-05dc-453c-85a4-efacb23a9cd3}{56}" paraid="1736585819">System Manager (process and application manager)&nbsp;</li>
	<li paraeid="{3a92dc90-05dc-453c-85a4-efacb23a9cd3}{63}" paraid="6430138">Password recovery (Firefox, IE, Chrome, Opera, Netscape,&nbsp;Seamonkey, Pidgin, Windows Live, Mozilla Thunderbird, Microsoft Outlook)&nbsp;</li>
	<li paraeid="{3a92dc90-05dc-453c-85a4-efacb23a9cd3}{70}" paraid="416733457">Keylogger&nbsp;</li>
	<li paraeid="{3a92dc90-05dc-453c-85a4-efacb23a9cd3}{77}" paraid="1159626126">Screen Capture (takes a JPEG image on demand or at specified intervals)&nbsp;</li>
	<li paraeid="{3a92dc90-05dc-453c-85a4-efacb23a9cd3}{84}" paraid="479086445">Remote Shell (cmd.exe or /bin/sh)&nbsp;</li>
	<li paraeid="{3a92dc90-05dc-453c-85a4-efacb23a9cd3}{91}" paraid="145239023">Reverse Proxy (hybrid SOCKS4/5 server that works with NAT)&nbsp;</li>
	<li paraeid="{3a92dc90-05dc-453c-85a4-efacb23a9cd3}{98}" paraid="2018572681">Proxifier&nbsp;</li>
	<li paraeid="{3a92dc90-05dc-453c-85a4-efacb23a9cd3}{105}" paraid="1543194885">HTTP Downloader (supports custom save location and name)&nbsp;</li>
</ul>

<p paraeid="{3a92dc90-05dc-453c-85a4-efacb23a9cd3}{112}" paraid="975462558">The&nbsp;NetWire&nbsp;payloads in all observed campaigns included nearly identical configurations.&nbsp;Specifically, the C2 domain clients[.]enigmasolutions[.]xyz&nbsp; and the password were&nbsp;the same.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>

<p paraeid="{3a92dc90-05dc-453c-85a4-efacb23a9cd3}{136}" paraid="1475054996">Example&nbsp;configuration&nbsp;listed below:&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>

<p paraeid="{3a92dc90-05dc-453c-85a4-efacb23a9cd3}{150}" paraid="439481653">C2List: clients[.]enigmasolutions[.]xyz:54578;&nbsp;</p>

<p paraeid="{3a92dc90-05dc-453c-85a4-efacb23a9cd3}{162}" paraid="1411313239">RC4_Key: c476b8e7afc13f4444cc71011019f21a&nbsp;</p>

<p paraeid="{3a92dc90-05dc-453c-85a4-efacb23a9cd3}{166}" paraid="2046070827">HostID: Cleint-SYeym4&nbsp;</p>

<p paraeid="{3a92dc90-05dc-453c-85a4-efacb23a9cd3}{172}" paraid="1855945546">Password:&nbsp;[redacted]&nbsp;</p>

<p paraeid="{3a92dc90-05dc-453c-85a4-efacb23a9cd3}{186}" paraid="2035464053">StartupKey:&nbsp;ruj&nbsp;</p>

<p paraeid="{3a92dc90-05dc-453c-85a4-efacb23a9cd3}{196}" paraid="305576382">KeylogPath: C:\Users\&lt; user &gt;\AppData\Roaming\msr\&nbsp;</p>

<p paraeid="{3a92dc90-05dc-453c-85a4-efacb23a9cd3}{210}" paraid="1047949688">LocalPath: %AppData%\Microsoft\MMC\ruj.exe&nbsp;</p>

<p paraeid="{3a92dc90-05dc-453c-85a4-efacb23a9cd3}{220}" paraid="1898481707">ProxyType: None&nbsp;</p>

<p paraeid="{3a92dc90-05dc-453c-85a4-efacb23a9cd3}{226}" paraid="2146779257">ConnectInterval: 30&nbsp;</p>

<p paraeid="{3a92dc90-05dc-453c-85a4-efacb23a9cd3}{232}" paraid="334072991">CopyToLocalPath: Yes&nbsp;</p>

<p paraeid="{3a92dc90-05dc-453c-85a4-efacb23a9cd3}{238}" paraid="1890446559">DeleteOriginalFile: No&nbsp;</p>

<p paraeid="{3a92dc90-05dc-453c-85a4-efacb23a9cd3}{244}" paraid="1613749906">LockExecutable: No&nbsp;</p>

<p paraeid="{3a92dc90-05dc-453c-85a4-efacb23a9cd3}{250}" paraid="608272589">AllowMultipleInstances: No&nbsp;</p>

<p paraeid="{9a387566-deaa-4235-aabe-50448c0ebf37}{1}" paraid="1845892858">OfflineKeyloger: Yes&nbsp;</p>

<p paraeid="{9a387566-deaa-4235-aabe-50448c0ebf37}{7}" paraid="613245477">&nbsp;<br>
The malware will establish persistence by adding an entry to the registry.&nbsp;For example,&nbsp;the&nbsp;NetWire&nbsp;malware&nbsp;value&nbsp;under the Microsoft Run registry&nbsp;“ruj” points to the&nbsp;NetWire&nbsp;payload in the&nbsp;AppData&nbsp;directory.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>

<p paraeid="{9a387566-deaa-4235-aabe-50448c0ebf37}{41}" paraid="2138775454">Key: HKEY_CURRENT_USER\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Run\ruj&nbsp;</p>

<p paraeid="{9a387566-deaa-4235-aabe-50448c0ebf37}{49}" paraid="1892530187">Data: C:\Users\&lt;user&gt;\AppData\Roaming\Microsoft\MMC\ruj.exe&nbsp;</p>

<h3 paraeid="{9a387566-deaa-4235-aabe-50448c0ebf37}{57}" paraid="1668822545">Conclusion&nbsp;</h3>

<p paraeid="{9a387566-deaa-4235-aabe-50448c0ebf37}{63}" paraid="544918020">On balance,&nbsp;the fall campaigns diverged from&nbsp;Bulgarian themed&nbsp;NetWire&nbsp;campaigns in the&nbsp;early&nbsp;summer in&nbsp;scope&nbsp;and scale.&nbsp;About half of the&nbsp;current recipients converged&nbsp;with&nbsp;and were included in&nbsp;the broader distribution&nbsp;observed earlier this summer.&nbsp;These campaigns distributed&nbsp;NetWire&nbsp;variants which used Bulgarian email lures, leveraged geofencing, and downloading EXEs through&nbsp;certutils.&nbsp;The low volume and tailored email lures&nbsp;suggest&nbsp;the actor&nbsp;put in effort&nbsp;to evade detection.&nbsp;The&nbsp;NetWire&nbsp;malware has been around since at least 2002 and has been consistently&nbsp;in use by various actors across&nbsp;the threat&nbsp;landscape.&nbsp;This&nbsp;analysis shows groupings of similar&nbsp;campaigns distributing&nbsp;NetWire&nbsp;based on message attributes, email lures&nbsp;and&nbsp;language, Office document metadata, VBA Macro code, and malware configuration.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>

<h3 paraeid="{9a387566-deaa-4235-aabe-50448c0ebf37}{165}" paraid="773425222">Indicators of Compromise (IOCs)&nbsp;</h3>

<table border="1" data-tablelook="1184" data-tablestyle="MsoTableGrid">
	<tbody>
		<tr role="row">
			<td data-celllook="0" role="rowheader">
			<p paraeid="{9a387566-deaa-4235-aabe-50448c0ebf37}{171}" paraid="1221555718"><strong>IOC&nbsp;</strong></p>
			</td>
			<td data-celllook="0" role="columnheader">
			<p paraeid="{9a387566-deaa-4235-aabe-50448c0ebf37}{176}" paraid="1575217839"><strong>IOC Type&nbsp;</strong></p>
			</td>
			<td data-celllook="0" role="columnheader">
			<p paraeid="{9a387566-deaa-4235-aabe-50448c0ebf37}{181}" paraid="951619988"><strong>Description&nbsp;</strong></p>
